ly what "spiritual" means, and it need have nothing to do with God.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aBrainvMiscellanea. 0aBrainxMiscellanea. 0aCognitive neuroscience. 0aNeuropsychology. 0aPsychology, Religious. 0aSpiritualityxPhysiological aspects. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Mind. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Science. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Mysticism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Psychology of Religion.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845716140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438457161423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438457161/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles